premise_source_doc_sentence: A soft-point bullet  (  SP  )  , also known as a soft-nosed bullet , is a jacketed expanding bullet with a soft metal core enclosed by a stronger metal jacket left open at the forward tip .
The driving band or rotating band is part of an artillery shell , a band of soft metal near the bottom of the shell , typically made of gilding metal , copper or lead .
They are usually made of a soft metal like lead , pewter , silver , brass , copper or tin .
Some weapons that operate at high rates of fire , such as the GAU-8 Avenger Gatling cannon , use plastic driving bands rather than soft metal .
Older burners were decorated with patterned combinations of soft metal pegs and brass tacks , often with mirrors in the panels of the upper part .
